“biological  agent”  means  any  microbial,  micro-organism,  virus  or 
infectious substance derived from them naturally or artificially, as well 
as their components and whatever their origin or method of production;

(b)  a  conveyance,  includes  every  person  acting  as  agent  for 
the owner or who receives freight or other charges payable 
in respect of the conveyance;

“relevant  Authority”  means  the  Authority  designated  under  the 
related laws for the regulation of the strategic items, unlisted items and 
restricted activities, and includes the Controller;

“technical  assistance”  includes  instructions,  skills,  training,  the 
provision  of  working  knowledge  and  consulting  services  and  may 
involve the transfer of technical data;

“technical  data”  includes  blueprints,  plans,  diagrams,  models, 
formulae, tables, engineering designs and specifications, manuals and 
instructions in print or electronic format;

“technology” means information and data in any form for the design, 
development, production or use of another item and includes technical 
data, technical assistance and software;

“toxin”  means  any  poisonous  substance,  whatever  its  origin  or 
method  of  production,  produced  by  a  living  organism  or  artificially 
synthesised which can cause illness, injury or death;

(b)  to  stop,  enter,  board,  inspect  and  search  any  place, 
premises,  structure  or  conveyance  and  to  detain  any 
conveyance;

(g)  the loading or unloading of any commodity, currency or 
person  contrary  to  the  customs,  fiscal,  immigration  or 
health laws of Malaysia;

(a)  an  inventory  specifying  the  description,  markings  and 
other particulars which clearly identifies the items seized 
has been prepared by an authorized officer;

(c)  to  prescribe  the  procedures  for  the  issuance  of  permits 
under  this  Act,  including  the  establishment  of  different 
classes of permits for different classes of strategic items;

(d)  to prescribe the procedures for the registration of brokers 
under  this  Act,  including  the  establishment  of  different 
classes of brokers for different classes of strategic items;

(g)  to  prescribe  the  forms  of  registers  to  be  kept  and 
maintained  by  permit  holders  and  registered  brokers, 
including the particulars to be recorded in the registers;
